INSERT INTO `pages` VALUES (96,'chris-kraus','chris-kraus','No Country For Odd Poets: Chris Kraus','No Country For Odd Poets: Chris Kraus','','<p>Chris Kraus is a writer, art critic and former filmmaker known for her anti-academic approach within an academic reception. In the 1980s she introduced a new series of books called Native Agents- publishing work by American authors such as Kathy Acker, William.S.Burroughs and Eileen Myles - to American publishing house Semiotext(e), well-known for being the first to translate radical French writers such as Jean Baudrillard and Michel Foucault into English.</p>\r\n<p>Her novels includeI Love Dick(1997),Aliens and Anorexia(2000) andTorpor(2006) as well as non-fiction booksVideo Green: Los Angeles Art and the Triumph of Nothingness(2004) andWhere Art Belongs(2011), all of which have been published by Semiotext(e). Her most recent publicationSummer of Hatewas published last year. The protagonists in her books are primarily real people within art scenes as well as the the author herself. Coincidentally, Chris Kraus is also one of the protagonists in Sunset Boulevard(2012) by Kevin Vennemann, who will our next guest at \'No Country for Odd Poets\' in May 2013.</p>\r\n<p>For this event Kraus will be reading from and talking about her novels. On Thursday 28 March 2013, she will be talking about her work with emphasis on film, at Lothringer13_Laden.</p>\r\n<p>Kraus is a Professor of Film at the European Graduate School in Saas-Fee, Switzerland. She lives and works in Los Angeles, USA.</p>',104,0,'[[{\"type\":\"basetext\"},{\"type\":\"imagegallery\",\"id\":532},0],[0,{\"type\":\"imagegallery\",\"id\":504},0],[0,0,0]]','<div id=\"container\" style=\"position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 1627px; height: 2243px; \"><div style=\"position: absolute; top: 91px; left: 91px; width: 470px; height: 1240px; \">\n            <h1 class=\"basetext\"><img src=\"/hlimages/104.jpeg\" alt=\"No Country For Odd Poets: Chris Kraus\"></h1>\n   